The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for time series forecasting, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of "deep learning" (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of clustering techniques to group similar time series together, which falls under the subfield of "unsupervised learning" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are a type of RNN, and therefore the paper could also be classified under the subfield of "neural networks" (cs.NE). The paper also involves the analysis of large datasets, which falls under the subfield of "data science" (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed methodology to benchmarking datasets, which could fall under the subfield of "evaluation" (cs.SI).
